(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)**America doesn’t care about energy, just the power that it generates.**

* (((
(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)**Bryce 2010 **(Robert, Author from the New York Times and Washington Post, “Power Hungry: The myths of “Green” Energy and the Real Fuels of the Future”)
)))

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)
**Since America doesn’t care where energy comes from, it comes at the expense of the people in this country.**

* (((
(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)Federal Government Energy Policy in Navajo Nation
)))

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-left: 0.5in; margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)**Russia Times America 2011** (“Navajo Nation Contaminated by Uranium Ore”, **0:24-1:27**, (% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(17, 85, 204); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)__http:~/~/www.youtube.com/watch?v=7DxWBFFkxwY__(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %))

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)
**Although we can’t see it, systems of oppression dehumanize the privileged community. Thus, dominant US identities remove their own humanity as they remove it from people such as the Navajo.**

* (((
(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)**Adams, Bell, and Griffin 2007 (**(Maurianne, Lee Anne and Pat, Professors at the University of Massachusetts Amherst, Barnard College, (% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)and University of Massachusetts,(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %) “Teaching for Diversity and Social Justice”)
)))

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)
\\**The Navajo Nation is continuing to lose its entire culture to dominant policy.**

* (((
(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)**Russia Times America 2011** (“Navajo Nation Contaminated by Uranium Ore”,** 1:53-2:23**,[[ &amp;#62;&amp;#62;url:http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7DxWBFFkxwY]][[(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(17, 85, 204); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)__http:~~/~~/www.youtube.com/watch?v=7DxWBFFkxwY__&amp;#62;&amp;#62;url:http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7DxWBFFkxwY]](%%))
)))

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)
\\**The US government isn’t doing anything to help the Navajo people.**

* (((
(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)**Russia Times America 2011** (“Navajo Nation Contaminated by Uranium Ore”, **2:49-3:14**, (% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(17, 85, 204); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)__http:~/~/www.youtube.com/watch?v=7DxWBFFkxwY__(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %))
)))

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman serif&amp;#34; %)
\\**Advocacy: The USFG should substantially reduce its restrictions it has placed on individuals as a result of its energy policy and begin practicing a policy of multicultural conservation. Just as the debate community should reduce its restrictions it has placed on individuals as a result of the exclusive practices within traditional debate and must begin a policy of multicultural conservation.**
